# Glowmint

Linux-native desktop app for Corsair hardware ‚Äî an iCUE alternative for Mint and other distros.

**Stack:** Tauri 2 (Rust backend) + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + Vite.

## Shared repo ‚Äî build for everyone

This repo is **public and cloned on other machines**. Changes must work for contributors and users on fresh checkouts ‚Äî not only the current dev environment.

| Principle | Do | Don't |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Portable setup** | Use `/setup` checks, `setup_probe`, and copy-paste commands that adapt to detected distro | Assume Mint, apt, or one developer's udev/systemd layout |
| **No machine lock-in** | Resolve paths at runtime (`which`, env, config store); document generic steps in README/CONTRIBUTING | Hardcode home dirs, usernames, repo paths, or "works on my box" one-offs |
| **Varied hardware** | Graceful empty/error states when Corsair devices or backends (OpenRGB, liquidctl, ckb-next) are missing | Require specific USB IDs or running daemons to use the app |
| **Distro breadth** | Prefer detection + manual instructions for dnf/pacman/unknown; apt auto-install via pkexec where supported | Ship Mint-only logic without a fallback for other distros |
| **Onboarding path** | Welcome wizard + Setup page are how new users get unblocked | Rely on `scripts/setup-mint.sh` alone ‚Äî it's a convenience script, not the product |

When adding features or fixing bugs, ask: *Would this work on a clean clone on Fedora, Arch, or Ubuntu with different Corsair gear and no local tweaks?* If not, add detection, docs, or UI guidance ‚Äî don't leave it implicit.

## Design

Glowmint‚Äôs look is **dark-mode glassmorphism**, inspired by Apple‚Äôs **Liquid Glass** (WWDC 2025): translucent layers that float above content, adapt to what‚Äôs behind them, and keep the hardware UI feeling fluid and premium ‚Äî not flat or boxy.

| Concept | What it means | Glowmint |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Glassmorphism** | Frosted-glass UI: semi-transparent surfaces + background blur for depth and hierarchy | `backdrop-filter: blur()` + low-opacity `rgba` tints |
| **Liquid Glass** | Apple‚Äôs adaptive glass material ‚Äî nav/controls sit in a distinct floating layer; tint and legibility respond to underlying content; fluid, borderless edges | Dark-first; glass for shell, cards, and bars ‚Äî content stays primary |
| Translucency | See-through panels, not opaque fills | `--glowmint-glass-*-bg` tokens in `src/index.css` |
| Layering | Functional glass above a rich canvas (gradients, depth) | `panel` / `inset` / `bar` variants on `GlassSurface` |
| Borders | Liquid Glass avoids hard strokes; depth from material, not outlines | **No borders** ‚Äî blur, tint, and subtle inset shadows only |

Use **`GlassSurface`** (`src/components/ui/GlassSurface.tsx`) for cards and panels ‚Äî apply glass via `--glowmint-glass-*` tokens in `src/index.css`, not opaque card fills.

**Component library.** Follow `.cursor/rules/component-library.mdc`: shared UI in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn/Radix primitives + Glowmint wrappers). Pages/features import from `components/ui`.

## User feedback (toasts)

Transient feedback ‚Äî "saved", "applied", and operation errors ‚Äî goes through the **toast alert server** (`src/components/ui/toast.tsx`), shown bottom-right. Import `toast` from `@/components/ui` and call it from hooks, pages, or features. `<Toaster />` is already mounted once at the app root (`src/App.tsx`) ‚Äî don't add another.

| Do | Don't |
| --- | --- |
| `toast.success('Canvas layout saved')` after an action succeeds | Track a `message` string in component state |
| `toast.error(String(err))` in `catch` blocks | Render `{message ? <p>‚Ä¶</p> : null}` inline |
| Match the variant to intent: `success`, `error`, `info`, `warning` | Show errors in success-colored text |

```tsx
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äî ad-hoc message state + inline paragraph (the pattern we removed)
const [message, setMessage] = useState<string | null>(null);
setMessage('Canvas layout saved');
{message ? <p className="text-sm text-emerald-200">{message}</p> : null}

// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äî publish to the toast server
import { toast } from '@/components/ui';
toast.success('Canvas layout saved');
```

Keep blocking or detailed output (install logs, multi-step progress) in a dialog or `ProgressSheet`; toasts are for quick, dismissible confirmations.

## App areas

| Route | Purpose |
| --- | --- |
| `/` (Dashboard) | Device overview, backend health, setup banner |
| `/aio` | Elite AIO LCD + pump/fan cooling |
| `/lighting` | RGB zones and lighting modes |
| `/peripherals` | Keyboards, mice ‚Äî RGB, DPI, profiles |
| `/setup` | System checks, udev rules, backend setup |
| Welcome wizard | First-run onboarding (blocks main app until complete/skipped) |

## Hardware backends

Not every install has every device or backend. UI and services should degrade cleanly (status, setup hints) rather than fail hard.

| Area | Backend | Driver path |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Elite AIO LCD | Native Rust HID | `src-tauri/src/drivers/corsair_lcd/` |
| Pump / fans | liquidctl | `src-tauri/src/drivers/liquidctl.rs` |
| RGB lighting | OpenRGB | `src-tauri/src/drivers/openrgb.rs` |
| Keyboards / mice | ckb-next | `src-tauri/src/drivers/ckb_next.rs` |

Profiles (save/load LCD, cooling, RGB settings) are persisted via `profile_service` + `profile_store`.

## Architecture

Layered flow: **React UI ‚Üí `src/lib/api.ts` (invoke) ‚Üí Tauri commands (`state.rs`) ‚Üí services ‚Üí drivers ‚Üí hardware**.

| Layer | Path |
| --- | --- |
| Pages | `src/pages/` |
| Feature UI | `src/features/` |
| API | `src/lib/api.ts`, `src/lib/types.ts` |
| IPC | `src-tauri/src/state.rs` |
| Services | `src-tauri/src/services/` |
| Domain | `src-tauri/src/domain/` (pure types/traits ‚Äî no Tauri/USB imports) |
| Drivers | `src-tauri/src/drivers/` |

See `CONTRIBUTING.md` for where new code goes and how to add a backend.

## Dev commands

Prerequisites (Node 20+, Rust, Tauri Linux deps) are in `README.md` ‚Äî verify those before assuming a local env issue.

```bash
npm install         # first-time / after pull
npm run tauri dev   # run app
cargo test          # Rust tests (from src-tauri/)
npm run lint        # eslint + prettier
```

New contributors: use in-app **Setup** (`/setup`) for system checks; `scripts/setup-mint.sh` is optional Mint-specific automation.
